The paper describes a system for machine translation of news text from Finnish to English using a Character Based Neural Machine Translation model. This falls under the category of Natural Language Processing (NLP) and specifically Machine Translation (MT), which is covered by cs.CL (Computation and Language) sub-category. The use of neural networks and deep learning techniques for MT also makes cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) a likely sub-category. The paper also mentions the use of BLEU score as an evaluation metric, which is commonly used in machine learning and optimization tasks, making cs.LG (Learning) another possible sub-category. The use of neural networks for MT also falls under the sub-category of cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Finally, the paper may also be relevant to the sub-category of cs.CV (Computer Vision) as it involves processing of text data.
